<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Simple Blog</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #fdf6e3; /* Light cream background */
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        header {
            background-color: #4682b4; /* Steel blue */
            color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .blog-post {
            background-color: #ffffff;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 15px;
            width: 80%;
            box-shadow: 0 0 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .blog-post h2 {
            color: #2e8b57; /* Green headings */
        }

        .blog-post p {
            font-size: 16px;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        footer {
            background-color: #4682b4;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        a {
            color: #b22222;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>Seanna's Blog</h1>
</header>

<div class="blog-post">
    <h2>My First Post</h2>
    <p>Welcome to my blog! This is my first post. I will be sharing interesting stories, tutorials, and experiences here.</p>
    <a href="#">Read more...</a>
</div>

<div class="blog-post">
    <h2>Traveling to Kollam</h2>
    <p>Kollam is a beautiful city in Kerala, India. Its backwaters, beaches, and cultural heritage make it a wonderful place to visit.</p>
    <a href="#">Read more...</a>
</div>

<div class="blog-post">
    <h2>Learning HTML & CSS</h2>
    <p>HTML and CSS are the building blocks of web development. With practice, you can create beautiful websites like this simple blog.</p>
